📁 Repository Setup
bash
Copy
Edit
git init                        # Initialize a local repo
git clone <repo_url>           # Clone a remote repo
📄 Staging and Committing
bash
Copy
Edit
git status                     # Show current changes
git add <file>                 # Stage specific file
git add .                      # Stage all changes
git commit -m "Your message"  # Commit staged changes
🔄 Pushing & Pulling
bash
Copy
Edit
git push                       # Push to default remote branch
git push -u origin <branch>    # Push and set upstream
git pull                       # Pull latest from default remote
🌿 Branching
bash
Copy
Edit
git branch                     # List branches
git branch <name>              # Create branch
git checkout <branch>          # Switch to branch
git checkout -b <branch>       # Create and switch
git merge <branch>             # Merge into current branch
🚮 Deleting Branches
bash
Copy
Edit
git branch -d <branch>         # Delete local branch
git push origin --delete <branch>  # Delete remote branch
🔍 Logs & History
bash
Copy
Edit
git log                        # Full commit history
git log --oneline --graph      # Compact view with branches
🧽 Undo & Reset
bash
Copy
Edit
git restore <file>             # Discard local file changes
git reset HEAD <file>          # Unstage a staged file
git reset --hard HEAD          # Discard all changes
🌍 Remote Management
bash
Copy
Edit
git remote -v                  # Show remotes
git remote add origin <url>    # Add new remote
git remote remove origin       # Remove remote
🔁 Sync Fork / Upstream
bash
Copy
Edit
git remote add upstream <url>
git fetch upstream
git merge upstream/main

